review_blob: This is a great cider.  It is really light, bubbly and crisp.  Apple flavor is not overpowering and doesnt leave a bad aftertaste.  It has just the right amount of carbonation.  I like ciders, but usually cannot drink more than one because they are generally too sweet.  Thats not the case with Wynkoops Western Slope Cider.  Its not nearly as sweet as a Woodchuck or Woodpecker.
